From: Hyun Kwon <hyun.kwon@xilinx.com>
Date: Tue, 18 Mar 2014 09:18:22 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 466/827] media: xilinx: vip: Add common sink/source pad IDs

This patch comes from:
  https://github.com/Xilinx/linux-xlnx.git

Add common sink/source pad IDs. As commented, IP cores with multiple inputs or
outputs should define their own IDs instead of using these values.

Signed-off-by: Hyun Kwon <hyunk@xilinx.com>
Acked-by: Laurent Pinchart <laurent.pinchart@ideasonboard.com>
Signed-off-by: Michal Simek <michal.simek@xilinx.com>
(cherry picked from commit 0afd780e03011d9501e980a5791cec356dae3008)
Signed-off-by: Zumeng Chen <zumeng.chen@windriver.com>
---
 drivers/media/platform/xilinx/xilinx-vip.h | 7 +++++++
 1 file changed, 7 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/media/platform/xilinx/xilinx-vip.h b/drivers/media/platform/xilinx/xilinx-vip.h
index 873d06e..e3b0032 100644
--- a/drivers/media/platform/xilinx/xilinx-vip.h
+++ b/drivers/media/platform/xilinx/xilinx-vip.h
@@ -25,6 +25,13 @@
 #define XVIP_MIN_HEIGHT			32
 #define XVIP_MAX_HEIGHT			7680
 
+/*
+ * Pad IDs. IP cores with with multiple inputs or outputs should define
+ * their own values.
+ */
+#define XVIP_PAD_SINK			0
+#define XVIP_PAD_SOURCE			1
+
 /* Xilinx Video IP Control Registers */
 #define XVIP_CTRL_CONTROL			0x0000
 #define XVIP_CTRL_CONTROL_SW_ENABLE		(1 << 0)
